{"author":"Michael Giver","data":{"body":"Implemented 2026-07-08 (branch giverm/OSCER-752-exclusion-determination-return-best; not yet committed/pushed).\n\n4-file change:\n- Rules::ExclusionRuleset — dropped age (`age_under_19` method + the two age params from `eligible_for_exclusion`); added explicit `EXCLUSION_FACT_IDS` bridge (fact name -> config id, no string-munging).\n- ExclusionDeterminationService — removed dead `extract_date_of_birth`/`extract_evaluation_date` + their facts; `highest_priority_reason_code` selects via `min_by { exclusion_priority(fact.name) }` (fail-loud `.fetch` on the bridge + `Exclusion.find`); passes `[reason_code]` to recording.\n- CertificationCase#record_exclusion_determination — now takes `reason_codes` (mirrors the existing `record_exception_determination` sibling); service owns selection.\n- Determination — deleted `to_reason_codes` (it was the old \"return unsorted list of all\" behavior; no direct spec).\n\nCollateral specs updated: exclusion_ruleset_spec (dropped `#age_under_19`, `eligible_for_exclusion` -> 3-arg), certification_case_spec + certification_business_process_spec (new reason_codes signature, removed dead fact lets).\n\nVerification: full suite 2549 ex 0 failures, 96.45% line / 83.46% branch cov, RuboCop clean. Net -235 lines. Spec contract: recorded determination `reasons` = single-element highest-priority array (incl. a config-override test proving priority is config-driven, not hardcoded). NEXT: /review then PR."},"env_id":"7fda8af9-5f39-45e1-9caf-59ffda62ec19","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783541461424202001,"uuid":"74087230-9451-489b-9138-07d1d180045b"}